HEADWORD: Pyrethrin
<hw>Pyr"eth*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Pyrethrum</ets>, generic name of feverfew, Gr. <?/ feverfew.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance resembling, and isomeric with,
ordinary camphor, and extracted from the essential oil of feverfew; --
called also <altname>Pyrethrum camphor</altname>.</def><-- a complex of
several substances. Used as insecticides. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

